</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-30_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-32_">Who are Skills for Care?

</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/who-are-skills-for-care--dr-richard-dune--1681466957120.png?v=1681466964" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/who-are-skills-for-care--dr-richard-dune--1681466957120.png?v=1681466964 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/who-are-skills-for-care--dr-richard-dune--1681466957120_500x.png?v=1681466964 320w" width="1981" height="1321" alt="Who are Skills for Care? - Richard Dune, PhD -" title="Who are Skills for Care? - Richard Dune, PhD -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-33_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-34_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-36_">In 2001, Skills for Care was established as the strategic body for planning and developing adult social care in England. Additionally, they worked with Health Education England and Skills for Health to establish the Care Certificate, which assesses the fundamental skills and knowledge needed in social care.
<br>
<br>Skills for Care envisions a society where social care users receive the care, support, and advice they need to live a whole and satisfying life. Skills for Care collaborates with health and social care employers, partners, and the government to accomplish this vision. By working together closely, Skills for Care can assemble a network of experts who can leverage their knowledge and influence to maximise its reach and impact.<br>
<br>For the social care sector to deliver high-quality care, collaborative working ensures it has the people, training, skills, and support it needs.
<br> 
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-37_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-39_">What does Skills for Care endorsement mean?

